      "span_text": "More generally, this term can be used to represent a rough lower boundary in simulations of the atmospheric boundary layer;  show that the use of a canopy drag term identical to equation (6) in large-eddy simulations of a neutral boundary layer led to a significantly improved representation of logarithmic mean wind profiles in the near-surface region over those predicted by a traditional wall stress modelling approach."
